# Backend workflow

## Run

From `backend/` with the venv active:

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8001
```

`--reload` covers handler/service edits. Restart manually after:

- Changes to `app/main.py` startup or `lifespan`.
- New Alembic revisions in `backend/migrations/`.

## Tests (pytest)

- Always run from `backend/` so pytest picks up `tests/conftest.py`.
- `conftest.py` writes a temp SQLite DB and sets test secrets — tests must
  never hit `backend/data/sqlite.db`.

```bash
pytest                          # full suite
pytest tests/test_<name>.py -x  # focused, stop on first failure
pytest -k <substring>           # filter
```

TDD loop: write/extend a test under `backend/tests/test_*.py`, get it red,
implement until green, then run the whole suite before handing off.

## Schema changes

- Models live in `backend/app/models/`.
- Generate a revision with `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<msg>"`,
  review the SQL, then commit migration + model together.
- Never edit a migration that has shipped; add a follow-up revision instead.

## Style

- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style (`db.execute(select(...))`, typed `Mapped[...]`).
- Keep handlers thin — push logic into `app/services/` and `app/providers/`.
- Provider integrations (OpenAI, Ollama, yfinance) must keep working with the
  fallback path; never assume a key is configured.
- Don't add narrating comments (`# import foo`, `# return result`); only
  comment non-obvious intent or trade-offs.
